# Code Language Rules

## CRITICAL: All code must be in English

- ALL code, comments, docstrings, variable names, function names, class names MUST be in English
- ALL print statements, log messages, user-facing text MUST be in English
- ALL error messages, warnings, info messages MUST be in English
- ALL documentation, README files, commit messages MUST be in English
- ALL test output, test descriptions, test names MUST be in English

## Prohibited
- Do NOT write any code in any language other than English
- Do NOT use non-English characters in code (except for string content that is part of the data/scenario content)
- Do NOT write comments in any language other than English
- Do NOT write variable/function/class names in any language other than English

## Data Content Exception
- Scenario prompts and user-facing content within scenarios may be in the language intended for the experiment
- This applies only to the actual text content of prompts/responses, not to code structure

## Enforcement
- When reviewing code, always check that all code elements are in English
- When creating new files, ensure all code is in English
- When modifying existing files, translate any non-English content to English

